// shop-alchemy.rdm
// =====================================================================
// A PF2e alchemist's shop: elixirs, bombs, poisons, tools. Reuses
// people, customers, prices. Entry table: [@AlchemyShop]
// Prices in COPPER (1 gp = 100 cp). PF2e consumables are level-priced;
// the values below are typical low-level prices. (~) marks approximations.

Title: Alchemy Shop
Use: people.rdm
Use: customers.rdm
Use: prices.rdm
Use: stock-count.rdm
Use: items-alchemy.rdm

// Optional inputs from a caller (e.g. Town Forge via the API's
// promptValues). Defaults keep the file working standalone.
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} alchemy
Prompt: shopName {}
Prompt: size {} town
Prompt: keeperName {}
Prompt: keeperRace {}
Prompt: keeperGender {}
Prompt: keeperAge {}
Prompt: keeperDesc {}
Prompt: custName {}
Prompt: custRace {}
Prompt: custDesc {}

Table: TF-AlchemyShop
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: m=[@Markup]
Set: owner=[when]{$prompt5}=[do][@PersonName][else]{$prompt5}[end]
Set: oanc=[when]{$prompt6}=[do][@Ancestry][else]{$prompt6}[end]
Set: odesc=[when]{$prompt9}=[do][@PersonDesc][else]{$prompt9}[end]
**[@AlchemyTitle]** *(alchemy in {$town})*\n&
**Proprietor:** {$owner}, a {$odesc} {$oanc} who is [@Personality].\n&
**Prices:** {$markupReason}.\n&
**On the shelves:**\n&
[@AlchemyStock]\n&
**{$owner} says:** "[@AlchemyQuote]"\n&
**Also here:** [@Customer]

// Caller-supplied name if given, else roll. Prefixed to avoid collision.
Table: AlchemyTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@AlchemyShopName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: AlchemyShopName
The [@AlcAdj] [@AlcNoun]
The [@AlcAdj] [@AlcNoun]
[@AlcNoun] & [@AlcNoun]
[@FamilyName]'s [@AlcNoun]
[@FamilyName]'s [@AlcNoun]
The [@AlcNoun] & [@AlcNoun]
[@AlcNoun] and [@AlcNoun]
The [@AlcFixed]

Table: AlcAdj
Bubbling
Smoking
Green
Careful
Curious
Quicksilver
Volatile
Hidden
Murky
Steaming
Brimming
Cloudy
Potent
Glass
Amber
Bittersweet
Caustic
Vaporous
Distilled
Measured

Table: AlcNoun
Retort
Alembic
Flask
Vial
Mortar
Pestle
Tincture
Tonic
Phial
Crucible
Cauldron
Still
Elixir
Draught
Decoction
Vapour
Salt
Reagent
Apothecary
Dispensary

Table: AlcFixed
Bubbling Retort
Smoking Alembic
Green Flask
Mortar & Pestle
Careful Measure
Tincture & Tonic
Last Antidote
Vial & Vapour

Table: AlchemyStock
{!n=={[@StockCount with {$prompt4}]}}[@{$n} AlchemyItemLine]

// PF2e consumable prices (copper), typical low-level entries.
Table: AlchemyItemLine
[@AlchemyItem]\n

Table: AlchemyItem
[@PF2eConsumable with {$prompt4}]

Table: AlchemyQuote
Read the label twice. There are no second mistakes here.
That one's for throwing, not drinking. Important difference.
Shaken, never warmed. Warm it and we both regret it.
I distil everything myself. No back-alley swill here.
Healing's dear this season — the herbs came up short.
Don't mix them in your pack. I've swept up after those who did.
A bomb's only as good as the arm that throws it.
Smell it if you like, but I'd advise against tasting.
